The Village Green is by far my favorite breakfast place in Montgomery County, and I mean countywide the Village Green has the best food, service and coffee consistently out of everywhere I've been.  Their staff are amazing, the waitresses manage the morning rush smoothly and know their returning customers favorite drinks and usual plates. Their coffee is always good, not a triple mocha something or other, just fresh and hot and somehow better than I can ever brew at home. Weekday mornings are the hidden secret when you can get a quiet table, I vote to move my office and project meetings here. And while their home fries with grilled onions are amazing, the last word must go to their chicken Phili cheese-steak, one delicious mouth watering bite after another!

My family and I have always gone here as a tradition. The food is delicious, well-priced, and arrives in a very timely manner. It’s a small place, so even on a Saturday or Sunday you’re likely to get a table straightaway.  It also has a lot of character. The decorations are super cute. And they put lots of jam on your table so you don’t have to ask.  If you’re wondering what to order, go before work early in the morning to start a blah day off right. They have a ridiculously low-priced weekday special that basically gives you a whole gigantic breakfast like you’d get at IHOP for nearly half the price.  I’d recommend parking at the Mr. Tire next door. If you go to the official Village Green Restaurant parking behind the building, you may never come back out. It’s really difficult to navigate back there and there’s not enough space for cars to go in and out.

The food itself was alright but could be a lot better, and quality too, as it shows in the taste. Unfortunately the coffee wasn't satisfying at all, so don't count on a tasty cup of joe.
